{{infobox Museum |name = Bosniak Institute |image = The Bosniak institute located in Sarajevo.jpg |image_upright = |map_type = |map_caption = |coordinates = {{coord|43.8601|18.4256|display=inline}} |established = 2001 |location = [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] |visitors = |director = [[Amina Rizvanbegovic Djuvic]] <!--|board= [[Zlatko Lagumdzija]], [[Fehim Škaljić]] --> |publictransit = |website = {{url|http://www.bosnjackiinstitut.ba/}} }}
The '''Bosniak Institute''' ({{lang-bs|Bošnjački institut}}) is a cultural center in [[Sarajevo]] focusing on [[Bosniak]] culture. It was established by former Bosnian Vice President [[Adil Zulfikarpašić]]. The institute is housed in a renovated sixteenth century [[Turkish bath]] and includes a library and an art center.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arhivsa.ba/ica2004/robert.htm |title=Archives and Cultural Memory under Fire: Destruction and the Post-war Nationalist Transformation |author=Donia, Robert J. |publisher=University of Michigan |accessdate=10 May 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917210622/http://www.arhivsa.ba/ica2004/robert.htm |archivedate=17 September 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Archives, Documentation, and Institutions of Social Memory: Essays from the Sawyer Seminar |last1=Blouin |first1=Francis X. |last2= William G. |first2=William G. |year=2007 |publisher=University of Michigan Press |isbn=0-472-03270-4 |page=399}}</ref> [[File:Salon 3.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The Bosniak Institute, established by one of the most prominent Bosniak intellectuals of the 20th-century, [[Adil Zulfikarpašić]], is an odyssey of huge collections of works of art that summarizes a wide spectrum of the Bosniak history and culture.]]
