{{for|Ruler of Mewar|Mokal of Mewar}}
'''Mokal''' is a sub clan of [[Sandhu]] [[Jat people|Jat]] found mainly in central [[Punjab (region)]]. There is also a village named as Mokal in [[Kasur District]] in the [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] province of [[Pakistan]].<ref name="NRB">[http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=14&dn=Kasur Tehsils & Unions in the District of Kasur - Government of Pakistan] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807195906/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=14&dn=Kasur |date=2011-08-07 }}</ref> It is part of [[Chunian Tehsil]] and is located at 30°46'60N 74°12'0E with an altitude of 178 metres (587&nbsp;feet).<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/PK/4/Mokal.html Location of Mokal - Falling Rain Genomics]</ref>

