{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
[[Image:Yomud rug.jpg|250px|right|thumb| mid 19th century - Yomut ensi (door hanging)]]
The '''Yomut carpet''' is a type of [[Turkmen rug]] traditionally handwoven by the [[Yomut]] or Yomud, one of the major tribes of [[Turkmenistan]].  A Yomut design, along with designs of the four other major tribes, such as Ersari and Tekke, is featured on the [[Coat of arms of Turkmenistan|coat of arms]] and the [[flag of Turkmenistan]].

